A link name allows screen readers to voice what the links does. If there is no link text or the `alt` text is blank, screen readers have nothing to read, so read out the URL instead. To add a name do one of the following:

  • Add an aria-labelledby attribute
  • Add an img alt attribute if the link contains an img element

1569 <h2>

1570 <strong>Find the Ideal Bathtub or Shower</strong>&nbsp;

1571 </h2>

1572 <p>Improve your bathroom with a new bathtub or shower, available in freestanding, drop-in, alcove, wall, and base&nbsp;styles. Browse our selection of showers and tubs by material, style, or features to find the perfect fit for your bathroom.&nbsp;</p>

1573 <h3>

1574 <strong>What Type of Bathtub or Shower&nbsp;is Right for Your Home?</strong>&nbsp;

1575 </h3>

1576 <p>Drop-in bathtubs are mounted to a surround or frame in a bathroom. The frame covers the tub, leaving just the inside and the rim of the tub exposed. Freestanding bathtubs are different in that tub is finished on all sides, not requiring a frame or surround.&nbsp;</p>

Each a element must contain text or an img with an alt attribute.

A link name allows screen readers to voice what the links does. If there is no link text or the `alt` text is blank, screen readers have nothing to read, so read out the URL instead. To add a name do one of the following:

  • Add text between the a element start and end tags
  • Add an aria-label attribute
  • Add an aria-labelledby attribute
  • Add an img alt attribute if the link contains an img element
